rComments: I have to admit Huggins explains the mechanics thoroughly. However, the tests were based more on calculations. Huggins will make sure you understand the concepts but in order to get a decent mark, you are better off taking other professor's class.

I'll try my best to give an unbiased comment. He knows his stuff VERY WELL, explains questions very clearly and listens to students' questions. He makes his lectures very interesting, in fact his lectures are the most interesting lectures I've been to. If I have to say something bad, it'll be that his office hours are very short.
Fun to look at, not fun to learn from. Cocky and totally useless in office hours or emails but he  is super hot.

This guy was simply an amazing prof, you seriously learn a lot from him. He knows his stuff really well and presents it in a very clear way. When you ask him a question, he doesn't stutter like other profs and gives you a very clear answer. His exam is a bit challenging, but if you study the material, you should be fine.
